  DHAKA TARA (THE CLOUD CAPPED STAR).It is a       
  biopic of a cultural activist named Nilkantha    
  (meaning who has loaded himself with poison).    
  The character is loosely based on the biography  
  of the Indian filmmaker stalwart Ritwik Ghatak.  
  The narrative is treated in a non linear fashion.
  The time perspective of the film is 1969 and     
  the story evolves centering the non conformist   
  protagonist in a mental asylum where he was      
